    "For the DSIS scores, the individual scores for two stimuli generated with different rate allocation strategies are considered as samples from two different distributions, and the one-tailed Welch t-test is applied to determine whether one population mean is higher than the other with a p-value of 0.05.",
    "For the PWC experiment, the difference between the JOD values between the same pair of stimuli is used, and a rate allocation strategy is considered to provide better quality if its JOD is higher than its counterpart with a difference equal to or larger than 1 JOD.",
    "The results are displayed in Fig. 14, where a solid arrow indicates that one rate allocation strategy achieves superior subjective quality than the other according to a given experiment.",
    "Otherwise, a dotted line is used.",
    "For JPEG Pleno, the relationship between allocation strategies defined in Fig. 6 is also added to the diagrams of Fig."
